 {"id":"bd-1e2","title":"Create integration test suite for component interoperability","description":"## Purpose and Rationale

Create integration tests that verify components work correctly together. While unit tests verify individual components and E2E tests verify the whole system, integration tests focus on component boundaries and interactions.

## Background

Integration bugs often occur at boundaries between components:
- Console + Theme interaction
- Renderer + Console interaction  
- DisplayContext affecting multiple components
- Config affecting all subsystems

## Test Scenarios

### 1. Theme-Console Integration

```rust
#[test]
fn test_theme_styles_applied_by_console() {
    let theme = FastMcpTheme::builder()
        .primary_color("#00ff00")
        .build()
        .unwrap();

    let tc = TestConsole::new_with_theme(theme.clone());
    tc.console().print("[primary]Test[/]");

    // Verify the custom color was applied
    let raw = tc.raw_output().join("");
    // Check for the ANSI code corresponding to #00ff00
}
```

